  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South Sudan RC COVID-19 Response Plan Contribution NLRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Juba, South Sudan</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The number of COVID-19 cases are in sharp daily rise in South Sudan since the beginning 2021, which raises alarm. As of 11 Feb 2021, the number of confirmed cases is 4,960 (of which 3,729 has recovered ) with a death toll of 71 . For a fragile country like South Sudan where only 41% of the population has access to basic water supply and 11% has access to sanitation coverage , COVID-19 is more than a health crisis and poses additional risks to livelihoods and access to basic services.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to:
Output 1 - Improved access to safe water through rehabilitation of water points 
Output 2 - Improved access to sanitation facilities through rehabilitation/ construction of toilets  
Output 3 - Increase community awareness on COVID-19 transmission through appropriate hygiene promotion activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This proposal will target 10,000 most vulnerable people in Juba with an objective of increasing access to basic WASH services thus contribute to reduction of COVID-19 transmission.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To contribute to the prevention and control of COVID-19 community transmission through increased access to safe water, sanitation and hygiene services including risk communication and awareness building through behavour change communication approach. This objective will be achieved through rehabilitation/installation of WASH facilities in the targeted communities as well as in the schools. This project will contribute to earmarked WASH activities within SSRC National COVID Plan.</narrative>
  </description>
